data.name: MsgPrivacyIntro1
data.value: This privacy statement has been created by EDS to demonstrate our firm commitment to Privacy and Data Protection. This commitment as to EDS activities on the Internet and intranet is implemented through the EDS Web Privacy and Data Protection Privacy Policy.

data.name: MsgPrivacyIntro2
data.value: In accordance with the EDS Web Privacy and Data Protection Policy, the following discloses our information gathering and dissemination practices for this Web site:

data.name: MsgPrivacyJuniors1
data.value: We do not intentionally invite data from Juniors (under the age of 13) to this site, but where we are aware of such submissions for educational purposes, we will treat such data as 'Sensitive Data'. Data known to be from Juniors and which is not specifically submitted for educational purposes will be immediately deleted.

data.name: MsgPrivacyNotification1
data.value: In the event of any changes by EDS of its EDS Web Privacy and Data Protection Policy that may impact the practices described on this Web site will be prominently posted on this site. In no event will any such changes to this policy apply with respect to data previously collected through this site. If at any point EDS Voice of the Employee decides to use personally identifiable information in a manner different from that which was stated at the time it was collected, they will notify you by e-mail, and you will be given a choice regarding your personally identifiable information being transferred.

data.name: MsgPrivacyRetention1
data.value: Data submitted to this site will only be kept as long as necessary. When its purpose has been fulfilled, it will be deleted confidentially and totally.

data.name: MsgPrivacySecurity1
data.value: This site is subject to the security and confidentiality requirements of the EDS Global Code of Practice for Privacy and Data Protection, EDS Enterprise Security Information System, EDS Code of Business Conduct and other such security policies as may be in place locally.

data.name: MsgPrivacyUse1
data.value: The site collects data through a comments form and will only be used to respond to your specific question or request. For this purpose we request your name, location, and your e-mail address.

data.name: MsgPrivacyUse2
data.value: We may use user IP addresses to help diagnose problems with our server and administer our Web site, to analyze trends, to track user movement and use, and to gather broad demographic information. Such data is not linked to any personally identifiable information. Data submitted to the site may be transferred within EDS, including to subsidiaries, in accordance with the EDS Global Code of Practice for Privacy and Data Protection.

data.name: MsgPrivacyUse3
data.value: Data submitted to this site will not be shared with or sold to any outside parties, unless specifically requested by the user; the only exceptions to this being in response to a court order or other legal obligation.
